<inglise> Commission Regulation (EC) No 1112/97 of 18 June 1997 adopting exceptional support measures for the beef market in Ireland in application of Decision 97/312/EC </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) NR 1112/97, millega v&otilde;etakse vastu veiselihaturu erakorralised toetusmeetmed Iirimaal otsuse 97/312/E&Uuml; kohaldamisel 18. juuni 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2222/96 (2), and in particular Article 23 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 veise- ja vasikalihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2222/96, (2) eriti selle artiklit 23, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by Decision 97/312/EC (3), the Commission approved a plan proposed by Ireland for measures to be implemented as regards bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) in that Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: otsusega 97/312/E&Uuml; (3) kiitis komisjon heaks Iirimaa esitatud kava k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis veiste spongioosse entsefalopaatia (BSE) puhul rakendatavate meetmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the principal elements of the plan are inter alia compulsory slaughter and destruction of suspect cases of BSE and, if confirmed, slaughter and destruction of all animals in herds where cases of BSE have occurred, and identification and slaughter of animals exposed to the same risks as the affected animals; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse kava p&otilde;hielementide hulka kuulub v&otilde;imalike BSE-taudi haigestunud loomade sundtapmine ja h&auml;vitamine ning, kui haigus on kindlaks tehtud, k&otilde;ikide sellistesse karjadesse kuuluvate loomade tapmine ja h&auml;vitamine, mille puhul on esinenud BSE-juhtumeid, ning selliste loomade identifitseerimine ja tapmine, keda ohustavad samad riskid kui nakatunud loomi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these measures involve serious disturbances in the market of Ireland; whereas it is therefore necessary to take exceptional measures to support that market; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuste meetmetega seonduvad t&otilde;sised h&auml;ired Iirimaa turul; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja v&otilde;tta selle turu toetamiseks erakorralisi meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate to establish a scheme co-financed by the Community authorizing Ireland to purchase the animals concerned with a view to killing and subsequently destroying them; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane kehtestada &uuml;henduse kaasfinantseeritav kava, millega Iirimaal lubatakse asjaomaseid loomi nende tapmise ning j&auml;rgneva h&auml;vitamise eesm&auml;rgil kokku osta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas provision should be made for laboratory examination of the brains from a sample of the animals slaughtered and for the use of a limited number of animals for research or educational purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada tapetud loomade ajust v&otilde;etud proovide laboratoorne uurimine ning piiratud hulga loomade kasutamine uurimis- v&otilde;i &otilde;ppe-eesm&auml;rgil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate, to provide for a Community contribution of 70 % of the purchase price paid by Ireland for each animal destroyed pursuant to this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane ette n&auml;ha, et &uuml;hendus katab iga k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt h&auml;vitatud looma kohta 70% Iirimaa poolt makstud ostuhinnast; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the purpose of establishing the animal's market value, Ireland should set up a system securing a fair and objective evaluation of each animal; </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaa peaks seadma looma turuv&auml;&auml;rtuse kindlakstegemiseks sisse s&uuml;steemi, mis tagab iga looma &otilde;iglase ja objektiivse hindamise; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, it is necessary to ensure that the animals concerned are killed and destroyed in a hygienic manner; whereas the price paid to producers should compensate them for not selling the animals in question; whereas those animals must therefore be prohibited from being marketed; whereas it is therefore necessary to specify the conditions for the destruction of those animals and the controls to be carried out by the Irish authorities; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja tagada, et asjaomaste loomade tapmisel ja h&auml;vitamisel peetakse silmas h&uuml;gieenin&otilde;udeid; tootjatele makstava hinnaga h&uuml;vitatakse neile k&otilde;nealuste loomade m&uuml;&uuml;mata j&auml;tmine; seep&auml;rast tuleb keelata k&otilde;nealuste loomade turustamine; seep&auml;rast on vaja t&auml;psustada k&otilde;nealuste loomade h&auml;vitamise ja Iirimaa asutuste poolt tehtava kontrolli tingimused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, so as to avoid mixing of the animals to be slaughtered pursuant to this Regulation with animals not covered by this Regulation and the occurrence of mistakes as to identity, they should be kept separately in the lairage to a slaughterhouse, as well as in the slaughterhouse itself; </inglise>
<eesti> v&auml;ltimaks k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel tapetavate loomade segunemist k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega h&otilde;lmamata loomadega ning vigu loomade identifitseerimisel, tuleks neid tapamaja lautades ja ka tapamajas hoida eraldi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, provision should be made for Commission experts to check compliance with the conditions as specified; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada komisjoni ekspertide v&otilde;imalus kontrollida nimetatud tingimuste t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Beef and Veal, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las veiseliha- ja vasikalihaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities in Ireland shall be authorized to purchase any bovine animal present on a holding located in the territory of Ireland which has not shown any clinical sign of BSE and is to be slaughtered in accordance with Ireland's eradication plan as approved by Decision 97/312/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaa p&auml;deval asutusel on luba osta k&otilde;iki Iirimaa territooriumil asuvates p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;tetes elavaid veiseid, kelle puhul ei ole ilmnenud BSE kliinilisi tunnuseid ja kes tapetakse otsusega 97/312/E&Uuml; heakskiidetud Iirimaa haigust&otilde;rjeprogrammi kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The animals referred to in paragraph 1 shall be killed in a specially designated slaughterhouse. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud loomad tapetakse selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud tapamajas. </eesti>
<inglise> The head, internal organs and carcases shall be permanently stained. </inglise>
<eesti> Pead, siseelundid ja r&uuml;mbad m&auml;rgistatakse h&auml;vimatu v&auml;rviga. </eesti>
<inglise> The stained material shall be transported in sealed containers to a specially authorized rendering plant for disposal in such a way that no part of it may be placed on the market. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;rgistatud materjal veetakse pitseeritud konteinerites eriloa saanud j&auml;&auml;tmetehasesse, kus see h&auml;vitatakse nii, et &uuml;htegi selle osa ei ole v&otilde;imalik turule viia. </eesti>
<inglise> No part of the abovementioned animals may enter into the human food or animal feed chains or be used for cosmetic or pharmaceutical products. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski eespool nimetatud looma osa ei tohi sattuda inimeste v&otilde;i loomade toiduahelasse, samuti ei tohi neid kasutada kosmeetika- v&otilde;i farmaatsiatoodetes. </eesti>
<inglise> A representative of the competent authorities in Ireland shall be present in the slaughterhouse referred to above in order to supervise the operations in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaa p&auml;deva asutuse esindaja on alati kohal eespool nimetatud tapamajas, et valvata k&otilde;nealuste toimingute j&auml;rele. </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to the necessary control, after being killed in the specially designated slaughterhouse, the animals shall immediately be transported to a rendering plant for processing and destruction. </inglise>
<eesti> Loomad veetakse vastavalt vajalikule kontrollile p&auml;rast selleks m&auml;&auml;ratud tapamajas tapmist viivitamata j&auml;&auml;tmetehasesse t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks ja h&auml;vitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the first subparagraph, the competent authorities in Ireland may allow the on-farm slaughter of an animal where existing animal welfare practice would require this. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata esimesest l&otilde;igust, v&otilde;ib Iirimaa p&auml;dev asutus lubada looma tappa p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;ttes, kui seda n&otilde;uab sel ajal kehtiv loomakaitsetava. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the first subparagraph, the hides of the animals referred to in paragraph 1 do not have to be stained or destroyed provided that they have been treated in such a way that they can only be used for leather production. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenemata esimesest l&otilde;igust, ei pea l&otilde;ikes 1 viidatud loomade nahku m&auml;rgistama ega h&auml;vitama, kui need on t&ouml;&ouml;deldud viisil, mis laseb neid kasutada &uuml;ksnes nahatoodete valmistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The slaughterhouses referred to in paragraph 2 shall be organized and operated in such a way as to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 2 viidatud tapamaju korraldatakse ja k&auml;itatakse viisil, mis tagab, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) no bovine animal intended for slaughter for human or animal consumption, is present in the slaughterhouse when animals are being slaughtered pursuant to this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> a) &uuml;kski veis, kes tapetakse inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks, ei oleks tapamajas ajal, kui loomi tapetakse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) where it is necessary for bovine animals to be slaughtered pursuant to this Regulation to be held in lairage, they shall be kept separate from bovine animals intended for slaughter for human or animal consumption; </inglise>
<eesti> b) kui k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt tapetavaid veiseid on vaja hoida laudas, hoitakse neid eraldi veistest, keda kavatsetakse tappa inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> and </inglise>
<eesti> ning </eesti>
<inglise> (c) where it is necessary for products derived from animals slaughtered pursuant to this Regulation to be stored, such storage shall be separate from any storage facility used for meat or other products destined for human or animal consumption. </inglise>
<eesti> c) kui k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt tapetud loomade tapasaadusi on vaja ladustada, asub ladu eraldi k&otilde;igist hoiuruumidest, mida kasutatakse inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks m&otilde;eldud liha v&otilde;i muude toodete hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities in Ireland shall: </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaa p&auml;dev asutus: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) notwithstanding paragraph 1, before processing and destruction, be authorized to conduct laboratory examination of the brains from a sample of animals slaughtered; </inglise>
<eesti> a) saab, olenemata l&otilde;ikest 1, loa tapetud loomade ajust enne loomade t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist ja h&auml;vitamist v&otilde;etud proove laboratoorselt uurida; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) be authorized, before processing and destruction, to use a limited number of animals for research or educational purposes; </inglise>
<eesti> b) saab loa kasutada enne tapetud loomade t&ouml;&ouml;tlemist ja h&auml;vitamist piiratud hulka loomi uurimis- v&otilde;i &otilde;ppe-eesm&auml;rgil; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) carry out the necessary administrative checks and effective on-the-spot supervision of the operations referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3; </inglise>
<eesti> c) viib l&auml;bi vajalikud halduskontrollid ning l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 osutatud toimingute kohapealse kontrolli </eesti>
<inglise> and </inglise>
<eesti> ning </eesti>
<inglise> (d) control those operations on the basis of frequent and unannounced inspections, in particular to verify that all material has been effectively destroyed. </inglise>
<eesti> d) kontrollib neid toiminguid sagedaste ja ette teatamata inspekteerimiste alusel, eelk&otilde;ige selleks, et veenduda, kas kogu saadud materjal on t&otilde;husalt h&auml;vitatud. </eesti>
<inglise> The results of these checks and controls shall be made available to the Commission on request. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuste kontrollide tulemused tehakse taotluse korral komisjonile k&auml;ttesaadavaks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The price in respect of the animal to be paid to producers or their agents by the competent authorities in Ireland pursuant to Article 1 (1) shall be equal to the objective market value in Ireland of each animal concerned established on the basis of a system of objective evaluation agreed on by the competent authorities in Ireland. </inglise>
<eesti> Looma hind, mille Iirimaa p&auml;dev asutus maksab artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt tootjatele v&otilde;i nende vahendajatele, v&otilde;rdub iga asjaomase looma Iirimaal kehtiva objektiivse turuv&auml;&auml;rtusega, mis tehakse kindlaks Iirimaa p&auml;deva asutusega kokkulepitud objektiivse hindamiss&uuml;steemi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community shall co-finance the purchase price paid by the competent authorities concerned for each purchased animal which has been destroyed in accordance with Article 1 at a rate of 70 %. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus katab iga vastavalt artiklile 1 h&auml;vitatud looma kohta p&auml;deva asutuse poolt makstud ostuhinnast 70%. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The conversion rate to be applied shall be the agricultural rate in force on the first day of the month of purchase of the animal in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatav &uuml;mberarvestuskurss on k&otilde;nealuse looma ostmise kuu esimesel p&auml;eval kehtiv p&otilde;llumajanduslik &uuml;mberarvestuskurss. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Ireland shall adopt all measures necessary to ensure full compliance with the provisions of this Regulation. It shall inform the Commission as soon as possible of the measures which it has taken and of any amendments thereto. </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaa v&otilde;tab k&otilde;ik k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tete t&auml;ielikuks j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud meetmed. <hi rend="sub"> iiri </hi> Iirimaa teavitab komisjoni v&otilde;etud meetmetest ja neis tehtud muudatustest esimesel v&otilde;imalusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities in Ireland: </inglise>
<eesti> Iirimaa p&auml;dev asutus: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) shall inform the Commission immediately, each time the plan approved by Decision 97/312/EC is applied, of: - the number of animals selected for slaughter, </inglise>
<eesti> a) teatab komisjonile viivitamata iga kord, kui rakendatakse otsusega 97/312/E&Uuml; heakskiidetud kava, k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt eelmise n&auml;dala jooksul: </eesti>
<inglise> - the number of animals slaughtered, </inglise>
<eesti> - tapmiseks v&auml;ljavalitud loomade arvu, </eesti>
<inglise> - the average market value of the animals slaughtered, </inglise>
<eesti> - tapetud loomade arvu, </eesti>
<inglise> pursuant to this Regulation during the previous week; </inglise>
<eesti> - tapetud loomade keskmise turuv&auml;&auml;rtuse; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) shall establish a detailed report of the controls which they carry out pursuant to the measures referred to in Article 3 and shall communicate it to the Commission each quarter. </inglise>
<eesti> b) koostab &uuml;ksikasjaliku aruande artiklis 3 viidatud meetmete alusel tehtud kontrollidest ja edastab selle kord kvartalis komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 9 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 (4), Commission experts, accompanied where appropriate by experts from the Member States, shall carry out, in collaboration with the competent authorities in Ireland, on-the-spot checks to verify compliance with all the provisions of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (4) artikli 9 kohaldamist, teevad komisjoni eksperdid koost&ouml;&ouml;s Iirimaa p&auml;deva asutusega ja vajaduse korral koos liikmesriikide ekspertidega kohapealseid kontrolle, et veenduda k&otilde;igi k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse s&auml;tete t&auml;itmises. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures taken pursuant to this Regulation shall be considered to be intervention measures within the meaning of Article 3 of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt v&otilde;etud meetmeid k&auml;sitatakse sekkumismeetmetena m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artiklis 3 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
